3. cs.SI (Signal Processing) - The paper talks about single-user detection and treating interference as noise, which are signal processing techniques used in communication systems. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper does not directly deal with multimedia, but the concept of interference channels is relevant to multimedia communication systems.
